Icon collections and Backgrounds
--------------------------------

   The standard icons aren't beautiful, indeed.  But there do exist some
beautiful icon collections.  I know of @{b}MagicWB@{ub} and @{b}NewIcons@{ub}.

   @{b}MagicWB@{ub} is Shareware. The icons are drawn beautiful in pastel with every
known trick. You also get a lot of good backgrounds which beautify
workbench windows and MUI programs.  Fine and good readable fonts replace
the clumsy topaz8 font.  You also get good icons for the ToolManager.  You
can find a test version of MagicWB on Aminet.

   @{b}NewIcons@{ub} is Freeware. The icons do have relative intensive colors and
are drawn as three dimensional objects floating slanted in space.  You can
find NewIcons on Aminet, @{b}util/wb/NewIcons.lha@{ub}.

