Pipe command support in AmigaShell
----------------------------------

   There is a little known and quite useful undocumented feature built in
the 2.04+ AmigaShell, that is, AmigaShell knows about the @{b}Pipe@{ub} command. By
setting the local variable @{i}_pchar@{ui}, you can use pipes without even entering
the Pipe command. AmigaShell will prepend it on the command line
automatically if it sees the pipe separator command specified by _pchar on
the command line.

   Thus, after the command:
         1> Set _pchar "|"

(1)

   the above examples can be used like this:
         1> List SYS: | More
             or
         1> List SYS: NOHEAD | Sort IN: OUT: | More

   Those familiar with the UNIX pipes will notice how the usage is very
similar to the UNIX pipe usage.

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1)  The quotes around the vertical bar are important, to avoid
AmigaShell interpreting the command as an attempt to use PIPE:, if @{i}_pchar@{ui}
is already set (for example if the Shell is started from within another
one).


@EndNode

