Troubleshooting
---------------

@{i}Q:@{ui}
     When I try the command @{b}List SYS: | More@{ub} I get an error
              PIPE: Unknown command

     I have @{b}PIPE:@{ub} mounted, what's wrong?

@{i}A:@{ui}
     AmigaShell is referring to the command @{b}Pipe@{ub} in the error, not the
     @{b}PIPE:@{ub} device. You haven't installed the commands in the ShellTools
     archive.

@{i}Q:@{ui}
     I get a requester that says
              Please insert volume PIPE: in any drive

     when I try any of the command examples.

@{i}A:@{ui}
     @{b}PIPE:@{ub} is not mounted. Try @{b}Mount PIPE:@{ub}. If that doesn't work, refer to
     your AmigaDOS manual or a friend that knows how to mount devices.

@{i}Q:@{ui}
     When I try any of the examples the More window pops up but nothing is
     shown/I get an error afterwards/More pops up a file requester.

@{i}A:@{ui}
     You are not using the standard AmigaOS @{b}More@{ub} command. Either use
     another name or install a command that supports pipes.  Possibilities
     are the C= More, Less, or Most for example.

@{i}Q:@{ui}
     With use of PIPE:, sometimes characters get lost. What happened?

@{i}A:@{ui}
     Up to OS 3.1, the queue-handler has some bugs which don't allow a
     really foolproof transmission of data.  A compatible replacement for
     the queue-handler can be founbd on Aminet, @{b}util/sys/HWGQueue.lha@{ub}.

@{i}Q:@{ui}
     None of these happen but it still doesn't work as you described.

@{i}A:@{ui}
     Are you using OS 2.04 later? Are you using the standard AmigaShell?
     Try with all extras disabled.


@EndNode

