What are files ending with ...?
===============================

   Most endings on FTP sites or Fish disks tell you that the file is
compressed and/or is an archive containing more than one file. Some
programs even archive whole disks. Frequently found endings and programs to
handle the related files are:
@{i}.sfx@{ui}
     Compressed archives which are included in an executable program: Just
     call the program and it will extract itself (sfx = self extract)

@{i}.lha@{ui}
@{i}.lzh@{ui}
     Compressed archives; recommended: LhA (@{b}util/arc/LhA_e138.run@{ub} on Aminet
     or Fish disk 715) or Lx (@{b}util/arc/lx100.lha@{ub} on Aminet), Unix version
     available (@{b}misc/unix/lha-1.00.tar.Z@{ub})

@{i}.dms@{ui}
     Disks compressed using DMS (@{b}util/arc/dms111.sfx@{ub} on Aminet or Fish disk
     406)

@{i}.zom@{ui}
     Disks compressed using Zoom (@{b}util/arc/Zoom_5.4.lha@{ub} on Aminet, Fish
     disk 682); an older version which you probably need for uncompressing
     PasTeX is found on Fish disk 459.

@{i}.zoo@{ui}
     Compressed archive; recommended: Zoo (@{b}util/arc/zpp2-10.lzh@{ub} on Aminet
     or Fish disk 527)

@{i}.Z@{ui}
@{i}.z@{ui}
@{i}.gz@{ui}
     Compressed files; recommended gzip (@{b}util/pack/gzip124x.lha@{ub} on Aminet),
