How do I Read and write MS-Dos disks?
=====================================

   No problem for owners of Workbench 2.1 or higher: The program CrossDos is
part of the Workbench. All you have to do is mounting the device @{b}pc0:@{ub} by
putting it into the drawer @{b}Devs:DOSDrivers@{ub} or by double-clicking the icon
in @{b}Sys:Storage/DOSDrivers@{ub}. Ms-Dos disks in drive @{b}df0:@{ub} can now be handled in
the usual manner replacing the word @{b}df0:@{ub} by @{b}pc0:@{ub}. For example the directory
can be shown with the command @{i}dir pc0:@{ui}.

   People still running Workbench 2.0 or lower need a program called @{b}MSH@{ub}.
You will find this on the Aminet (directory misc/emu) and on Fish disk 382.
See @{"Sources" Link "Sources"}. After editing the file @{b}devs:MountList@{ub} as described in the
documentation you have to say @{i}Mount msh:@{ui} in the CLI and can now do the same
as above replacing the word @{b}pc0:@{ub} with @{b}msh:@{ub}.


@EndNode

